    <name>AsyncObjects Framework</name>
    <description>The AsyncObjects framework simplifies writing asynchronous event-driven dataflow-based applications in
        Java, Groovy, and Scala. It mainly builds upon ideas and syntax of E programming language. However, it also
        draws ideas from other programming languages like Occam and frameworks like SEDA as well. In addition to core
        library that supports common asynchronous communication patterns. The framework provides a wrapper for NIO-based
        sockets that simplify creation of network applications that support a high number of concurrent connections.
    </description>

